The paper deals with graph modification problems and homomorphism-based properties of edge-coloured graphs, which are topics commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of switching operations and signed graphs also suggests a possible categorization in computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of parameterized complexity, which is a topic studied in both computational complexity and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the study of graph homomorphism problems also has connections to graph theory (cs.GT).
